@page "/portfolio/eitr"

<PageTitle>Eitr - Fydar</PageTitle>

<HeadContent>
    <meta name="description" content="description">
</HeadContent>

<MainFullscreen>

    <section class="parallax-frame parallax-focalanchortop" style="--animation-time: 0.5;">

        <video class="parallax-layer" style="--parallax-multiplier: 0.5" autoplay muted loop>
            <source src="/media/eitr/background.720p.29fps.h265.mp4?v=1" type='video/mp4; codecs="hev1.1.2.L93.90"; profiles="isom,iso2,mp41"'>
            <source src="/media/eitr/background.720p.29fps.h264.mp4?v=1" type='video/mp4; codecs="avc1.4d401f"; profiles="isom,iso2,avc1,mp41"'>
        </video>

    </section>

    <section class="landing-footer">

        <picture>
            <img class="titlecard" src="media/eitr/titlecard.png?v=1" alt="Title card for the game 'Eitr'." style="image-rendering: pixelated;" />
        </picture>

        <SteamPlayButton href="https://store.steampowered.com/app/350050/EITR/">Visit on Steam</SteamPlayButton>

    </section>

    <section class="container">

        <p>I joined the indie title <i>‘Eitr’</i> team as a remote programmer. I programmed many core gameplay systems such as the <b>inventory system</b>, <b>item system</b>, <b>tooltips</b>, <b>character stats</b>, <b>skill trees</b>, <b>input mapping</b>, and <b>achievements</b>.</p>

        <Callout Type="primary">
            <Icon><SvgSprite Link="/icons.svg?v=1#icon-seal-check-fill" Alt="Check" /></Icon>
            <ChildContent>Working on this project inspired me to work on my personal projects. Some of them can be found below.</ChildContent>
        </Callout>

        <CardGrid Size="md">
            <Card AspectRatio="4/3" href="/portfolio/fydarbehaviour">
                <FeaturedImage>
                    <SvgSprite class="card-image" Link="/icons.svg?v=1#icon-nodeeditor" />
                </FeaturedImage>
                <ChildContent>
                    <div class="card-container">
                        <div class="row">
                            <SvgSprite class="card-keyicon" Link="/icons.svg?v=1#icon-fydarbehaviour" Alt="An illustration of the node based editor." />
                            <div class="column">
                                <h3 class="card-header"><span class="subtle">Fydar.</span>Behaviour</h3>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="row">
                            <p class="card-description"><b>Data-driven</b> and <b>flexible</b> <b>node-based</b> behaviour engine for items, abilities, quests, enemies, achievements, and more.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </ChildContent>
            </Card>
            <Card AspectRatio="4/3" href="/portfolio/fydarinventory">
                <FeaturedImage>
                    <SvgSprite class="card-image" Link="/icons.svg?v=1#icon-inventory" />
                </FeaturedImage>
                <ChildContent>
                    <div class="card-container">
                        <div class="row">
                            <SvgSprite class="card-keyicon" Link="/icons.svg?v=1#icon-fydarinventory" Alt="An illustration of the inventory system." />
                            <div class="column">
                                <h3 class="card-header"><span class="subtle">Fydar.</span>Inventory</h3>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="row">
                            <p class="card-description">Complete item and inventory system with transactions, constraints, equipment, tooltips, and more.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </ChildContent>
            </Card>
        </CardGrid>

        <p class="heading-prefix">Tooling for</p>
        <h2>Skill Tree Editing</h2>

        <p>I created a skill tree editor that is capable of editing a large quantity of nodes.</p>

        <figure class="figure-image">
            <picture>
                <img src="/media/eitr/skill-tree-editor-1-w900.jpg?v=1" alt="A screenshot of my skill tree editor editing a large skill tree." loading="lazy" />
            </picture>
            <figcaption>A skill tree for ‘Eitr’ inspired by those from <a href="https://www.pathofexile.com/">‘Path of Exile’</a>.</figcaption>
        </figure>

        <p>The skill tree went through multiple iterations thanks to the tooling provided.</p>

        <figure class="figure-image">
            <picture>
                <img src="/media/eitr/skill-tree-editor-2-w900.jpg?v=1" alt="A screenshot of my skill tree editor editing a smaller skill tree." loading="lazy" />
            </picture>
            <figcaption>A skill tree for ‘Eitr’ inspired by Nordic runes.</figcaption>
        </figure>

        <Callout>
            <Icon><SvgSprite Link="/icons.svg?v=1#icon-seal-check-fill" Alt="Check" /></Icon>
            <ChildContent>The editor was able to provide all the tools necessary to explore different styles.</ChildContent>
        </Callout>

    </section>

</MainFullscreen>
